assemblage.p:
A  rational function is one of the form
 f(x)=\frac{P(x)}{Q(x)}
where  P(x) and  Q(x) are polynomials and  Q(x)\neq 0.

li.p:
To obtain a concentration of 50/%, we solve C(x)=0.50:
\begin{aligned} C(x) \amp= 0.50 \\ \dfrac{2+x}{8+x} \amp= 0.50 \\ 2+x \amp= 0.50(8+x) \\ 2+x \amp= 4 + 0.50x \\ 0.5x \amp= 2 \\ x \amp= 4 \end{aligned}
He needs to add 4 ml.
